text:
<@U28TLDP0R> flurry of trello! high-level:
 - i put my thoughts down on features i want to have for an "alpha" release that we can give to the people in this slack. let's get those wrapped up and your other items and then do an internal release.
 - while people are reviewing that, then i want you to start working on "premium account" feature. The reason I want this to be the "first feature" albeit lame, i want to be able to test how many people are willing to give us money for just supporting us, without some sort of special feature available to them. I have some other ideas for features that use user accounts, but i think this can be first... then we can release those features to the premium account hlders for beta access

alpha tagged = what i want done for internal release
beta = what i want done for external release

attachments.fallback: Tom commented on determine the list of perks we are willing to give out to users: "@donaldminer Interesting question. One way to answer it would be to just look at the margin on each of the things we're selling, which seems to range between 50-60% of retail and go from there. So if we started anywhere south of 40% off, we wouldn't be losing money. But we're paying for me, and for our shipping minion, and for shipping supplies, too; so we should probably be a little conservative until we get an idea of volume. I think 10-20% would be fine, and probably more if there's a premium membership depending what it costs. We could also just do free shipping instead of/in addition to a discount."
